text.tspan: Daily vs. total confirmed COVID-19 cases per million people
Shown is the 7-day rolling average of confirmed COVID-19 cases per million people. The number of confirmed cases
is lower than the number of total cases. The main reason for this is limited testing.
Source: Johns Hopkins University CSSE COVID-19 Data
